26 August 1428":"26 August 1428","1408":"1408","1428":"1428","Wethersfield, Essex, England":"Wethersfield, Essex, England","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Wiggenhall, East Walton, & Terrington Howards, Norfolk, England":"East Walton, Norfolk, England","Harting, Sussex, England":"Harting, Sussex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hussey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: of Norman origin, a nickname for someone who habitually wore a distinctive pair of boots or gaiters, from Old French <i>hosed</i>, <i>hoset</i>, <i>housé</i>, Middle English <i>hosey</i>, <i>hus(s)y</i>,‘booted, gaitered’ (from Latin <i>hosatus</i>).","English: status name or nickname from Middle English <i>hus(e)wyf</i> ‘mistress of a family; wife of a householder’ (a compound of Old English <i>hūs</i> ‘house’ + <i>wīf</i> ‘woman’). Though originally a woman's name, it is often found as a male surname, presumably in a derogatory sense. The vocabulary word became <i>hussie</i>, with the meaning ‘disreputable woman’, in the 16th century; the surname, however, is not associated with this meaning.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’. This was the name of a bardic family associated with the Maguires of Fermanagh, also Anglicized as   Oswell   or   Oswald  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hosea","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  . Similarity with the Old Testament prophet's name Hosea (see 3 below) is accidental.","English: in Scotland, where the name is more common, it is sometimes a variant of   Hosie  , itself a form of   Hussey  , or else a variant of   Hossack  .","African (mainly Nigeria and Tanzania): from the Biblical personal name <i>Hosea</i>. In the Old Testament, Hosea was a prophet who married a prostitute in order to illustrate Israel's unfaithfulness to God."]},{"name":"Hosie","meanings":["Scottish (northeast Scotland): variant of Irish   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Hassey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Oswell","meanings":["English: variant of   Oswald  .","Irish (Ulster): adopted as an English equivalent of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’ (see   Hussey  )."]},{"name":"Hosey","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary Hussey was born in 1398, in Harting, Sussex, England, her father, Henry Hussey of Harting, was 59 and her mother, Margeria Holbrook, was 53. She had at least 1 daughter with Henry Howard of Wigenhall. She died after 1447, in East Walton, Norfolk, England."},"et":{"1398–after 1447":"1398–pärast 1447","1385–1470":"1385–1470","1398–1447":"1398–1447","1387–1436":"1387–1436","1428–1483":"1428–1483","1340–1408":"1340–1408","1345–1410":"1345–1410","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","9 October 1410":"9. oktoober 1410","1436":"1436","1447":"1447","after 1447":"pärast 1447","14 February 1436":"14. veebruar 1436","12 July 1408":"12. juuli 1408","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","1398":"1398","1387":"1387","26 August 1428":"26. august 1428","1408":"1408","1428":"1428","Wethersfield, Essex, England":"Wethersfield, Essex, England","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Wiggenhall, East Walton, & Terrington Howards, Norfolk, England":"East Walton, Norfolk, England","Harting, Sussex, England":"Harting, Sussex, England"},"fi":{"1398–after 1447":"1398–1447 jälkeen","1385–1470":"1385–1470","1398–1447":"1398–1447","1387–1436":"1387–1436","1428–1483":"1428–1483","1340–1408":"1340–1408","1345–1410":"1345–1410","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1483":"1483","14